Here’s how I made my dream gallery wall come true on plaster walls (and they work on drywall too).  What are your fave hanging methods? 

Besides the magical 3M velcro strips, I used ‘plaster picture hangers’ and ‘monkey hooks’.

You don’t even need any tool for monkey hooks, just wiggle them through. Yes, even on plaster (though you could drill a tiny pilot hole to make it easier). And they hold 100lb. 

The plaster picture hangers just hammer in and hold a variety of weight depending on if they are a single, double or triple nail. 

Here’s what they look like behind the wall using my fancy cardboard mock-up. Don’t forget the poster putty so they don’t shift around.

These make hanging double sawtooth frames SO quick and easy! You just put one on each sawtooth and your level on top of the frame; raise your frame so the center of the art is about eye level (which will bring it to within that range between 55-60” off the floor that’s the general rule of thumb); press on it so the little points puncture the wall; and then when you pull the frame away, the holes for your nails are already started! Takes under a minute!
